            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x51EA481<!--I love birds, and our pet crow is practically like another child to me. I've spent years researching their history from Grim's aviary to the way their "crow collective" behaves. Unfortunately, I also pushed too hard when trying to understand what happens if you provoke them. It was a terrible mistake, and I regret it in more ways than one. --></T>
                  <T>0x7EA440C9<!--I confess, I don't like opening up a lot unless I know people well. You seem mostly harmless, but I like to make sure I know all the ins and outs of a situation or a person before I get too involved. Plus, around here you get a lot of ghost nonsense pushed on you if you talk to the wrong people. I don't believe in ghosts, really, and don't want them around even if they do exist. You saw my sign, right?--></T>
                  <T>0x90EB50F0<!--Ekade is pushing me to start trying to talk to other Sims about my "condition" after our crow attacked me. I've been going to Afterlife Anonymous to try and understand Ghost Sims, but I confess that I'm as confused as ever. They keep acting like I'm one of them!--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="enabled">
              <T n="enabled">0xEBB55930<!--Ravenwood Rumors--></T>
            </V>
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
        <L n="tests">
          <L>
            <V t="relationship">
              <U n="relationship">
                <U n="relationship_score_interval">
                  <T n="upper_bound">32</T>
                </U>
