              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x8987E0C5<!--I bet you joke about it behind my back a bit, but of course I am working on settling with the reality of my situation after I was attacked by a crow. Sometimes a Sim can know the truth of a thing in their heart but it's just too shameful or difficult to show it outwardly. I'm working on it, but while some personality traits can feel really changeable, sometimes it's hard to make yourself want to change.--></T>
                  <T>0x9A91AABB<!--Some say people meet and be together in more than one lifetime. That feels a little overly optimistic to me, but I've heard that it does indeed exist. What I was told is that it would take a lot of work to convince your former loved one. It seems far-fetched, but as I said: I've heard about it from Sims I know!--></T>
                  <T>0xF0343489<!--That Waylon Warez weirdo over by the crypts has annoyed me for years. I don't care what he's trying to foist on gullible buyers, I've got better things to do with my time. Do I seem like a guy who wants to be friends with many ghosts?--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
